<bibRefCitation id="EFC7789C6275FFC770862BB8FBA5FC45" author="Schrottky, C." box="[909,1097,986,1010]" pageId="47" pagination="225 - 239" refId="ref37524" refString="Schrottky, C. 1908. Nuevos himenopteros. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina 65 (4): 225 - 239." type="journal article" year="1908">Schrottky (1908)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from a female specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="4992CB8F6275FFC7779D2B99FD00FB83" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="47">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34145FD6275FFC771FD2C7EFCD5FB83" box="[758,825,1052,1076]" name="Brazil" pageId="47">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and the type now lost (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7789C6275FFC777352C7EFCC6FBE2" author="Rasmussen, C. &amp; B. R. Garcete-Barrett &amp; R. B. Goncalves" pageId="47" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref37364" refString="Rasmussen, C., B. R. Garcete-Barrett, and R. B. Goncalves. 2009. Curt Schrottky (1874 - 1937): South American entomology at the beginning of the 20 th century (Hymenoptera, Lepidoptera, Diptera). Zootaxa 2282: 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="2009">Rasmussen et al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
). It has been widely recognized that 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE6275FFC771A62C3DFCE5FBC1" box="[685,777,1119,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
