</taxonomicName>
(whose type is also lost, see below), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE6275FFC770D72CE2FB50FB20" authority="Mitchell" authorityName="Mitchell" authorityYear="1930" box="[988,1212,1151,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis">
<emphasis id="B922D97F6275FFC770D72CE2FC18FB20" box="[988,1012,1152,1175]" italics="true" pageId="47">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B922D97F6275FFC7770A2C1DFBB6FB20" box="[1025,1114,1151,1175]" italics="true" pageId="47">aequalis</emphasis>
Mitchell
</taxonomicName>
are synonyms (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7789C6275FFC7708D2CC3FBBDFB0E" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; G. A. R. Melo &amp; A. DalMolin" box="[902,1105,1184,1209]" pageId="47" pagination="917 - 1001" refId="ref37121" refString="Moure, J. S., G. A. R. Melo, and A. DalMolin. 2007. Megachilini Latreille, 1802. In J. S. Moure, D. Urban, and G. A. R. Melo (editors), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical region: 917 - 1001. Curitiba: Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, xiv + 1058 pp. [updated online (http: // www. moure. cria. org. br / catalogue), accessed 31 July 2018]" type="book chapter" year="2007">Moure et al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Accordingly, we here designate as 
<typeStatus id="54EDBBCF6275FFC770D82CA0FBC7FB6D" box="[979,1067,1218,1242]" pageId="47">neotype</typeStatus>
the 
<typeStatus id="54EDBBCF6275FFC777502CA0FB50FB6D" box="[1115,1212,1218,1242]" pageId="47">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE6275FFC771C72C81FCA3FB4C" authorityName="Mitchell" authorityYear="1930" box="[716,847,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis">
<emphasis id="B922D97F6275FFC771C72C81FD08FB4D" box="[716,740,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="47">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B922D97F6275FFC771FE2C81FCA3FB4C" box="[757,847,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="47">aequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the only surviving type specimen for the three species-group names involved) thereby rendering these names as objective synonyms and stabilizing their nomenclatural application.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
