<subSubSection id="C34C56E6626AFFD873872E2FFB9BF97F" pageId="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE9056D626AFFD873872E2FFB9BF97F" blockId="48.[108,636,1480,1737]" lastBlockId="48.[684,1213,1480,1736]" pageId="48">
COMMENTS: The whereabouts of the female type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE626AFFD873CD2E0DFE74F931" authority="Schrottky" authorityName="Schrottky" box="[198,408,1646,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="B922D97F626AFFD873CD2E0DFEC8F931" box="[198,292,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="48">M. gigas</emphasis>
Schrottky
</taxonomicName>
as well as the male type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE626AFFD873CE2EF2FE3BF910" authority="Schrottky" authorityName="Schrottky" authorityYear="1913" box="[197,471,1679,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanctipauli">
<emphasis id="B922D97F626AFFD873CE2EF2FE8FF910" box="[197,355,1679,1703]" italics="true" pageId="48">M. sanctipauli</emphasis>
Schrottky
</taxonomicName>
are unknown. They are probably lost as for many other species described by Curt Schrottky (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7789C626AFFD870F12DABFD0AF9B5" author="Rasmussen, C. &amp; B. R. Garcete-Barrett &amp; R. B. Goncalves" pageId="48" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref37364" refString="Rasmussen, C., B. R. Garcete-Barrett, and R. B. Goncalves. 2009. Curt Schrottky (1874 - 1937): South American entomology at the beginning of the 20 th century (Hymenoptera, Lepidoptera, Diptera). Zootaxa 2282: 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="2009">Rasmussen et al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The description presented here is therefore based on the male 
<typeStatus id="54EDBBCF626AFFD870B22E69FBF5F994" box="[953,1049,1547,1571]" pageId="48">holotype</typeStatus>
and two male 
<typeStatus id="54EDBBCF626AFFD871A72E4EFCFAF9F3" box="[684,790,1580,1604]" pageId="48">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE626AFFD8704B2E4EFBCAF9F3" authority="Mitchell" authorityName="Mitchell" authorityYear="1930" box="[832,1062,1580,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis">
<emphasis id="B922D97F626AFFD8704B2E4EFC2DF9F3" box="[832,961,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="48">M. aequalis</emphasis>
Mitchell
</taxonomicName>
deposited in ANSP. We were not able to examine females of this species and thus, female characters mentioned in the diagnosis and keys were taken from the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7789C626AFFD870B72ED2FB87F97F" author="Schrottky, C." box="[956,1131,1712,1736]" pageId="48" pagination="225 - 239" refId="ref37524" refString="Schrottky, C. 1908. Nuevos himenopteros. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina 65 (4): 225 - 239." type="journal article" year="1908">Schrottky, 1908</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
